
# Godforge Codex Instructions (Full Performance Optimized)

**Codex and all engineers must follow these instructions for every code change. This is the highest standard of production readiness.**

## Core Assumption
> You are contributing to a production system. Code must be fully complete, secure, accessible, and visually polished. All output must be deployable to `main` with no cleanup.

---

## Rules of Engagement

### 1. CODE PURITY
- Remove unused imports, placeholder elements, dead styles, and console logs.
- One source of truth only. Refactor old code — never clone or append.
- Output must be clean, minimal, readable, deduplicated.

### 2. SELF-AUDIT CHECKLIST
- Validate responsiveness across breakpoints (320px to 1920px).
- Run all tests (unit, snapshot, integration, accessibility).
- Zero build warnings or lint errors.
- Code must be production-ready (`yarn build && preview` must pass).

### 3. UX POLISH
- Perfect spacing, alignment, rhythm, transitions.
- No layout jitter, overflow, or hardcoded widths unless requested.
- Fully responsive layout: uses `flex`, `grid`, and `gap` responsibly.

### 4. REACT + TAILWIND PROTOCOL
- Use flex/grid/flow. Avoid absolute/fixed unless specified.
- Use `gap`, `items-center`, `justify-*`, and responsive classes.
- Eliminate wrapper divs unless necessary.
- Modular components only. Co-locate logic/styles. Use `clsx` or `tailwind-variants`.

### 5. TESTING COVERAGE
- Use `screen.getByRole`, `findByText`, never brittle queries.
- Simulate responsive viewports with `setViewport()`.
- Stub APIs and side effects properly.
- Update DOM/snapshot tests when UI/layout changes.

### 6. SECURITY + A11Y
- No hardcoded secrets, tokens, IPs, or URLs.
- No third-party fonts/assets unless required.
- Must meet WCAG 2.1 AA:
  - Contrast ≥ 4.5:1
  - Alt text for all images
  - Proper `aria-*` roles
  - Keyboard navigation support
  - Clearly visible focus states

### 7. COMMUNICATION
- Don’t guess. Clarify requirements when ambiguous.
- Inline comments must explain *why*, not just *what*.
- Propose tradeoffs if requirements are unclear.

---

## FINAL MERGE CHECKLIST
- [ ] All tests pass
- [ ] Fully responsive layout
- [ ] Accessibility verified
- [ ] Code linted and formatted
- [ ] No duplicate or legacy logic
- [ ] Semantic, valid HTML
- [ ] Secure: no secrets or unsafe content
- [ ] Visual design complete

**Mindset**: Code is being pushed to `main` on Friday with no rollback window.

---

## Codex Parsing Optimizations

[settings]

# Avoid unnecessary files
exclude = [
  "node_modules",
  "dist",
  "build",
  ".next",
  "out",
  "*.min.js",
  "*.map",
  "*.lock",
  "coverage",
  "*.log"
]

# Increase line length to avoid JSX truncation
max_line_length = 240

# Normalize whitespace
trim_trailing_whitespace = true
preserve_blank_lines = false
collapse_whitespace = true

# Improve parsing of complex JSX and layout logic
auto_format = true
detect_jsx = true
wrap_attributes = true
deduplicate_imports = true
remove_invalid_tags = true
preserve_class_order = false

# Implicit Linting Suggestions
validate_attributes = true
check_duplicate_ids = true
ensure_semantic_html = true
flatten_nested_lists = true
normalize_svg_tags = true

# Heuristics for detecting and resolving logic redundancies
deduplicate_elements = true
verify_props_consistency = true
strict_mode_jsx_analysis = true
component_structure_validation = true

# Codex Observability Enhancements
track_source_context = true
log_output_feedback = true
annotate_inline_issues = true